The paper deals with the problem of matching skull images with face images, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). It also involves forensic applications, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of a database, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed approach involves transform learning, which is a technique used in multimedia processing (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact of the research on law enforcement, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
